commit.message: Back to development: 1.4.2
Preparing release 1.4.1

Fix string formatting after catching error

After changes how pydot called graphviz, bug with printing
"debug" info about called process was introduced.
There were missing variables left after this refactor.

Fixes: #201

Make attributes order deterministic

Attributes of nodes, edges and graphs were random since they were
kept in a dictionary. Now when converting them to strings, they
are sorted so they will always be in the same order.
Use .gitignore from Github's template for Python
Fixed ChangeLog
Back to development: 1.4.1
Preparing release 1.4.0

Fix code not working with Python 2.7

setup.py have code not working with Python 2.7, which was typing

Change way of obtaining package version

Importing pacakge to get version might have unexpected side effects.
The most important one is simply fail to exec setup.py due to
not beign able to import some of the dependencies that are used by the
package.
To avoid that, simple regexp looking for __version__ string is used.

Use README as package description

It is a good practice to have nice and complex package description
on PyPI to help future users to decide if this is what they are looking
for. To have it "for free" just use README file. Since PyPI now
supports Markdown, it is even easier.

Add support of Windows' conda installations

On conda/anaconda Graphviz is called using .bat files due to some
customizations made on that platform [1].

[1] https://github.com/conda-forge/graphviz-feedstock/blob/24a27a82edc23ea0581f9ee5b2c757fba66907b1/recipe/bld.bat#L26)

Fix comparing of SHA hash in regression tests

In 2d55978511fc548dcb989d5553435f8e11c9aead bug in tests were introduced.
When running regression tests, test suite compares outputs
of graph parsed (and rendered) by pydot and rendered directly by
graphviz. To compare, test suite uses SHA hash of the outputs.
The bug was using *the same* SHA hash (of pydot output) when comparing
outputs. This caused regression tests usless.
After fixing this problem, failing regression tests were discovered and
will be gradually fixed.

Update URLs to Travis CI

After transferring `pydot` to organisation, URLs to Travis build has been changed.
Additionally it has been migrated grom travis-ci.org to travis-ci.com due
to https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/open-source-on-travis-ci-com

Run tests on AppVeyor in conda env

Conda/Anaconda is the most popular way of installing pydot on
Windows environments.
Removed useless packages from requirements.txt
Update URLs
Back to development: 1.3.1
Preparing release 1.3.0

Add setup.cfg with wheels and zest.releaser

`pydot` wheels are universal and this is needed to be placed
in setup.cfg
Included configruation for `zest.releaser` to make releases
easier.
Update maintainer information in setup.py

Back to development: 1.3.0

ChangeLog has been updated

Move errno from os to builtin. Fixes #177

os.errno has been removed in Python 3.7

See: https://bugs.python.org/issue33666
Use HTTPS and update redirects
Fix typos
Replace 3.7-dev with 3.7 final

Build tags, master and PRs only once

Added condition that will allow Travis to build only master
PRs and tags and only once.
Upgrade Python syntax with pyupgrade https://github.com/asottile/pyupgrade
Drop support for EOL Python 2.6
REL: bump version to 1.2.5
DOC: correct typo
